    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Other">
        <prj:name>First polarization observations of disk of a proto-brown dwarf candidate L328-IRS</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We propose the first high angular resolution dust polarisation observations of a disk detected by ALMA (cycle 2) forming around a proto-brown dwarf candidate L328-IRS. This source is currently forming in a subcore of L328 core. Proposed observations will probe the magnetic field morphology for the first time in a disk of a candidate proto-brown dwarf and would give us an important clue regarding the role of the magnetic fields in the disk formation and evolution. The results obtained from these observations will help us in providing the constraints to the models proposing the disk formation around substellar objects. </prj:note>
