        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>This is a polarization observation. We simply need to set up the correlator for continuum observation mode.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The disk size is about 0.8" x 0.6", Our proposed angular resolution of 0.3" for the polarization measurement will be enough to diagnose its structure over the disk within a resonable amount of observing time. The largest angular scale is not important for our main purpose of the proposal.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Our cycle 2 ALMA measurement of the peak intensity in the disk  is 6.4 mJy per beam of 0.31"x0.24".
Considering a typical 1% polarization of the flux in the disk, expected polarized flux would be 64 microJy/beam. 
Our observation with a sensitivity level of 11  microJy will detect the polarized flux with S/N~6.
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
